{
  "doc_id": "39449",
  "text": "Gel strength as described by [CITATION_1] was measured by Bloom determinations using a TA-XT2 Texture Analyzer. An 11% protein solution was made (3.2 g of dried sample mixed with 26.7 mL of deionized water and 3.3 mL of 0.03 M CaCl 2 , and allowed to sit for 15 min. To initiate gelation, the sample was heated to 80°C for 30 min in a water bath, cooled in an ice bath for 15 min, and then stored overnight at 4°C. Gel strength was determined using a 0.5-inch analytical probe to a depth of 6 mm at the rate of 1 mm/s.",
